Title: Beyond Therapy / Lust in the Dust

reviewText: I got this two movie disc for Lust In The Dust as it was cheaper this way than on it's own.  This is an excellent western comedy that should give most people a few good laughs.  Beyond Therapy I tried but couldn't find anything funny about it.  For me this is still a good buy.
summary: One out of two ain't bad

Title: Beyond Therapy / Lust in the Dust

reviewText: When I bought this, I was looking for a reasonably priced copy of "Lust in the Dust".  When I saw this combo, I thought that I would take a chance, buy it, and pray for the best on the movie "Beyond Therapy".  That was a major mistake!  "Beyond Therapy" is a homophobe's dream movie with so many horrible cliches that it is sickening!  I will avoid watching it.  As for "Lust in the Dust", well what can I say?  C'mon, a movie with Divine, Tab Hunter, and Rita Moreno!  How can you go wrong?  But...having said that, if you can't afford the $25-$35 price range that some sellers are charging, get this.  Otherwise, do as I sometimes do and don't buy it and pray that the price will eventually go down.
Title: Beyond Therapy / Lust in the Dust

reviewText: Lust in the Dust is classic. It might be totally inane humor, but you laugh inspite of yourself. One of the last staring roles by Tab Hunter, a 50's hunk...it has outrageous performances. Beyong therapy is quirky, but also very funny
